OL,6,FMs Ramos described her sister as
OL,7,Fsomeone who was very athletic, who had
OL,8,Fbeen a Spanish long jump champion at
OL,9,F18, was also academically clever,
OL,10,Fwinning a scholarship to university.
OL,12,FShe said her sister gave her time to
OL,13,Fhelp others, including supporting
OL,14,Fvulnerable people to complete the
OL,15,FCamino De Santiago pilgrimage.
OL,17,FShe also expressed gratitude for all
OL,18,Fthe letters her family had received
OL,19,Ffrom people in Ireland following her
OL,20,Fsister's death.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/12
